## Q27
Question:
The relationship between the voltage (V) applied to an X-ray tube and the maximum frequency of the X-rays emitted from the target is defined by:
Option A:
Duane Hunt Law
Option B:
Reciprocity law
Option C:
Inverse square law
Option D:
All of the above
Correct Answer:
A
Difficulty:
Medium
Explanation:
The Duane-Hunt law relates the maximum energy (and thus the maximum frequency) of the X-ray photons produced in an X-ray tube to the accelerating voltage applied across the tube. It states that the maximum energy corresponds to a photon created when an electron loses all its kinetic energy in a single interaction.
