## Q36
Question:
Concept of annihilation photons is used in:
Option A:
CT
Option B:
MRI
Option C:
USG
Option D:
PET scan
Correct Answer:
D
Difficulty:
Medium
Explanation:
Positron Emission Tomography (PET) relies on the emission of positrons from an injected radiotracer. When a positron meets an electron, they annihilate each other, producing two 511 keV gamma photons traveling in opposite directions. The PET scanner detects these coincident photons to localize the radioactive source.
