## Q42
Question:
The parallel component in an ultrasonic beam beyond which it disperses is called:
Option A:
Fresnel zone
Option B:
Fraunhofer zone
Option C:
Pressure zone
Option D:
All of the above
Correct Answer:
A
Difficulty:
Hard
Explanation:
The ultrasound beam emitted by a transducer is divided into two parts. The near field, characterized by parallel beam lines and a relatively constant diameter, is the Fresnel zone. Beyond this, the beam enters the Fraunhofer zone (far field), where it begins to diverge (disperse) from the central axis.
