Option A:
MRI
Option B:
Ultrasound
Option C:
Computed radiography
Option D:
Digital radiography
Correct Answer:
C
Difficulty:
Medium
Explanation:
Computed Radiography (CR) utilizes a photostimulable phosphor (PSP) plate as the image receptor. When exposed to X-rays, the phosphor traps energy in a latent image. When scanned by a laser in the reader, this trapped energy is released as light, which is then captured and digitized to form the image.
