Question:
Characteristic curve shifts towards ________ for shorter development time.
Option A:
Left
Option B:
Right
Option C:
No change
Option D:
Down
Correct Answer:
B
Difficulty:
Hard
Explanation:
Development time directly affects film speed. Shortening the development time results in less silver reduction, making the film less sensitive. On a characteristic curve plot (Density vs. Log Exposure), a decrease in speed causes the curve to shift toward the right, meaning more exposure is required to reach the same density.
