## Q50
Question:
Single coated X-ray films are used in all of the following except:
Option A:
Mammography
Option B:
CT films
Option C:
Skull X-ray
Option D:
Fluoroscopy
Correct Answer:
C
Difficulty:
Medium
Explanation:
Mammography, CT, and fluoroscopy (spot films) utilize single-emulsion (single-coated) films to maximize resolution, as parallax error is eliminated. Conversely, standard diagnostic radiography, such as a routine skull X-ray, uses double-emulsion film to maximize the speed of the film-screen system and reduce patient dose, as resolution requirements are less stringent.
